author: Adam Savage’s Tested
description:
Adam Savage visits the Lucasfilm campus to pay a visit to some of the surviving models and miniatures he worked on for Steven Spielberg's A.I. Artificial Intelligence (2001)! It's a walk down model shop memory lane for Adam as he shows us the details he and the model team put into the ruins of New York skyscrapers, and the tricks they used to make these practical effects look so convincing on film. Plus, an intricate miniature Adam built that never made it to the final cut of the movie!

Shot by Joey Fameli and edited by Norman Chan
Music by Jinglepunks
Additional media courtesy of ILM
